---
/**
 * Time / Identity Stem: foundational layer (Notion Core Concepts 18.07.2026).
 * Content aligned with Identity Differential synthesis + official structure.
 */
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ConceptPageHero from '../../components/concepts/ConceptPageHero.astro';
import ConceptPager from '../../components/concepts/ConceptPager.astro';
import { getConcept } from '../../lib/concepts';

const c = getConcept('time');
---

<Layout title={`${c.title} | Identity Engineering`}>
	<main class="min-h-screen">
		<ConceptPageHero
			scene={c.scene}
			tag={`${c.tag} · ${c.layerLabel}`}
			title={c.title}
			lede={c.blurb}
			scrollHint={c.scrollHint}
		/>

		<section class="border-t border-white/10 px-6 py-24">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
				<div class="mb-4 text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-white/40">Why Time first</div>
				<h2 class="mb-6 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white md:text-4xl">
					The stem is a temporal object — defined by ongoing tension.
				</h2>
				<div class="space-y-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-white/55">
					<p>
						<strong class="text-white/80">Time</strong> is the foundational layer. The <strong class="text-white/80">Identity Stem</strong> only exists through the continuous integration of two directed forces that stand in fundamental tension:
					</p>
					<ul class="space-y-3 pl-1">
						<li class="flex gap-3">
							<span class="text-cyan-400/80">←</span>
							<span><strong class="text-white/75">State Differential</strong> (past → present): the drive toward <strong class="text-white/80">Sameness-as-Trajectory</strong></span>
						</li>
						<li class="flex gap-3">
							<span class="text-violet-400/80">→</span>
							<span><strong class="text-white/75">Vision Gradient</strong> (present → future): the drive toward <strong class="text-white/80">Causal Entropy</strong> (maximizing future freedom)</span>
						</li>
					</ul>
					<p class="mt-4">
						This is the original, foundational <strong class="text-white/80">Spannung</strong> of identity: the ongoing negotiation between preserving coherence with one’s history and actively opening new degrees of freedom. All further tension (relational, collective, high-dimensional) builds on this basic polarity.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="border-t border-white/10 px-6 py-24">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-28">
				<div>
					<div class="mb-3 text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-cyan-400/70">01 · Past</div>
					<h2 class="mb-6 text-3xl font-bold text-white md:text-4xl">State Differential</h2>
					<p class="mb-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-white/60">
						The observed derivative of the state: <code class="text-violet-300">δS = dS/dt</code> (or discrete ΔS). This is the causal chain of actual changes from the past up to now.
					</p>
					<p class="mb-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-white/60">
						It maximizes <strong class="text-white/80">Sameness-as-Trajectory</strong>. After change, we are not recognizable from the current snapshot (that is copyable). We are recognizable from the transparent history of how we moved.
					</p>
					<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-white/60">
						<strong class="text-white/80">Engineering work:</strong> Make the State Differential transparent and owned. The past is not a fixed story to defend. It is a verifiable causal chain that can still authenticate the entity after radical change.
					</p>
				</div>

				<div>
					<div class="mb-3 text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-violet-400/70">02 · Present</div>
					<h2 class="mb-6 text-3xl font-bold text-white md:text-4xl">State</h2>
					<p class="mb-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-white/60">
						<code class="text-violet-300">S(t)</code>: the high-dimensional state vector right now (competencies, relationships, inner states, positions, resources…).
					</p>
					<p class="mb-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-white/60">
						The present is only the <strong class="text-white/80">current cross-section</strong> of the Stem. It is where past trajectory meets future gradient. It is never the full definition of identity.
					</p>
					<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-white/60">
						<strong class="text-white/80">State ≠ Identity.</strong> The present state is always embedded in and shaped by the ongoing tension between backward coherence and forward freedom.
					</p>
				</div>

				<div>
					<div class="mb-3 text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-cyan-400/70">03 · Future</div>
					<h2 class="mb-6 text-3xl font-bold text-white md:text-4xl">Vision Gradient</h2>
					<p class="mb-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-white/60">
						<code class="text-violet-300">V ≈ ∇𝒞</code>, where 𝒞 is causal entropy: a measure of future freedom of action.
					</p>
					<p class="mb-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-white/60">
						In Identity Engineering, <strong class="text-white/80">Vision</strong> is the intended gradient of causal entropy. It points where future freedom of action increases most steeply. This forward drive stands in permanent productive tension with the backward pull of Sameness-as-Trajectory.
					</p>
					<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-white/60">
						<strong class="text-white/80">Engineering work:</strong> Sharpen the Vision Gradient. Make the direction of steepest ascent of freedom clear, strong, and owned — while keeping it coherent with the State Differential.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="border-t border-white/10 bg-white/[0.02] px-6 py-24">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
				<div class="mb-4 text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-violet-400/70">Integration</div>
				<h2 class="mb-8 text-3xl font-bold text-white md:text-4xl">The Full Stem — Held in Tension</h2>

				<p class="mb-8 text-lg leading-relaxed text-white/60">
					Identity (the complete stem) is the <strong class="text-white/80">integrated Worldline</strong> that holds the fundamental tension between backward coherence and forward freedom in productive balance:
				</p>

				<ul class="mb-12 space-y-4 text-lg text-white/60">
					<li class="flex gap-3">
						<span class="text-cyan-400">←</span>
						<span><strong class="text-white/80">Backward:</strong> State Differential → Sameness-as-Trajectory</span>
					</li>
					<li class="flex gap-3">
						<span class="text-violet-400">→</span>
						<span><strong class="text-white/80">Forward:</strong> Vision Gradient → Causal Entropy</span>
					</li>
				</ul>

				<div class="mb-12 overflow-x-auto rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-black/40 p-8 font-mono text-sm text-violet-200/90">
					I = arg max_γ [ ∫<sub>now</sub><sup>future</sup> V(γ(t)) · dγ  +  λ · Coh(γ, δS<sub>past</sub>) ]
				</div>

				<p class="mb-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-white/60">
					The parameter <code class="text-violet-300">λ</code> expresses the ongoing trade-off — the core Spannung — between opening future freedom and maintaining coherence with past trajectory. This tension is not a problem to solve but the defining condition of the Identity Stem.
				</p>

				<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-white/60">
					Identity Engineering works on two primary levers:
				</p>
				<ol class="ml-2 mt-4 list-inside list-decimal space-y-3 text-lg text-white/60">
					<li>Transparency and ownership of the <strong class="text-white/80">State Differential</strong>.</li>
					<li>Clarity and force of the <strong class="text-white/80">Vision Gradient</strong>.</li>
				</ol>

				<p class="mt-8 text-lg leading-relaxed text-white/60">
					Rotation then stabilizes this axis under tension. Mass gives it the substance to bear tension. Frequency makes the quality and dynamics of the tension describable.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="border-t border-white/10 px-6 py-24">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
				<h2 class="mb-8 text-3xl font-bold text-white md:text-4xl">Why this matters in the AI era</h2>
				<p class="mb-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-white/60">
					Static snapshots of identity become cheap and copyable. What remains authentic is the <strong class="text-white/80">signed history of differentials</strong> — a chain that starts from a unique human origin and continues through freedom-maximizing updates. Observation of change itself constitutes ongoing identity.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<ConceptPager id="time" />
	</main>
</Layout>

<style>
	code {
		font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, monospace;
		background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		padding: 0.15em 0.4em;
		border-radius: 4px;
		font-size: 0.9em;
	}
</style>
